Overview

This project applies unsupervised machine learning techniques to classify satellite images using clustering algorithms implemented from scratch in Python.
The following methods were compared:K-Means, K-Means with Mahalanobis Distance, Fuzzy K-Means, Fuzzy K-Means with Mahalanobis Distance, RGB and HSV color spaces
The goal is to segment the image into 5 clusters based on color similarity.

Technologies : Python, NumPy, OpenCV, Matplotlib, Methods, K-Means

Clusters pixels by minimizing the distance between pixels and cluster centroids.
Mahalanobis Distance : Improves clustering by considering covariance between features:

Fuzzy K-Means allows pixels to belong to multiple clusters with different membership values, improving segmentation in mixed regions.

Results
HSV features improved region separation.
Mahalanobis distance improved clustering performance.
Fuzzy K-Means produced smoother segmentation boundaries.
Best results were achieved using Fuzzy K-Means with Mahalanobis Distance.
